quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  72,1,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “It was revealed to me that a band of unseen beings{1}listened in and said, ‘Indeed, we have heard a wondrous Recital{2}",1:[The Arabic word used is <i>jinn</i> which are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.],2:[The Arabic word used is <i>Qur’an</i> which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.]
  72,2,"that guides to prudence, so we have come to believe in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord."
  72,3,"And that{1}most high is the Grandeur of our Lord—He never took a female companion nor a child.",1:[Qira’at: All except for Ibn ‘Amer, Abu Ja’far, Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “And indeed…”]
  72,4,"And that<sup>d </sup>our fool used to speak untruthfully about Allah."
  72,5,"And that{1}we thought that humans and unseen beings would never say{2}a lie aboutAllah.",1:[Qira’at: All except for Ibn ‘Amer, Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “And indeed…”],2:[Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…would never attribute a lie to Allah.”]
  72,6,"And that<sup>d </sup>certain men among humans used to seek refuge in certain men among the unseen beings, but they only increased them in confusion."
  72,7,"And that<sup>a </sup>they thought, as you<sup>pl </sup>thought, that Allah would never resurrect anyone."
  72,8,"And that<sup>a </sup>we sought to reach the heaven and found it filled with stern guards and meteors."
  72,9,"And that<sup>a </sup>we used to take up positions to listen in, but whoever listens now finds a meteor in wait for him."
  72,10,"And that<sup>a </sup>we do not know whether ill has been desired for those on earth, or if their Lord has desired prudence for them."
